AIM: 
To write a C program to search for an element in an array using the Linear Search method. 
 
 
ALGORITHM: 
1. Start the program. 
2. Declare variables: arr[], n (size), key (element to search), and i. 
3. Read n from the user. 
4. Read n elements into the array arr[]. 
5. Read the search element key. 
6. Loop from i = 0 to n-1: 
 If arr[i] == key, display position and stop the search. 
7. If not found after the loop, display “Element not found”. 
8. Stop the program. 
 
 
PROGRAM 
#include <stdio.h> 
int main() { 
int arr[50], n, i, key, found = 0; 
printf("Enter number of elements: "); 
scanf("%d", &n); 
printf("Enter %d elements:\n", n); 
for (i = 0; i < n; i++) { 
scanf("%d", &arr[i]); 
} 
printf("Enter the element to search: "); 
scanf("%d", &key); 
for (i = 0; i < n; i++) { 
if (arr[i] == key) { 
printf("Element %d found at position %d.\n", key, i + 1); 
found = 1; 
break;  
} 
} 
if (!found) { 
printf("Element %d not found in the array.\n", key); 
} 
return 0; 
} 
 
